& [SourceSet] is the checked research surface
  + [source_001] is Evan Miller, Finite-time blowup for a Navier-Stokes model equation for the self-amplification of strain
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.05415
    = relevance: isolates strain self-amplification and shows blowup in a model sharing important strain/enstrophy structure with full Navier-Stokes
  + [source_002] is Evan Miller, A regularity criterion for the Navier-Stokes equation involving only the middle eigenvalue of the strain tensor
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.05569
    = relevance: identifies the positive middle strain eigenvalue as a scale-critical regularity/blowup coordinate
  + [source_003] is Evan Miller, On the interaction of strain and vorticity for solutions of the Navier-Stokes equation
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.02691
    = relevance: studies the reverse interaction of vorticity on strain and gives regularity criteria clarifying depletion by advection
  + [source_004] is Johnson and Meneveau, On the role of vorticity stretching and strain self-amplification in the turbulence energy cascade
    = url: https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-fluid-mechanics/article/on-the-role-of-vorticity-stretching-and-strain-selfamplification-in-the-turbulence-energy-cascade/1E302903363C67A09F9B9E817533F935
    = relevance: reports that non-local pressure Hessian and viscous terms alter the finite-time tendency seen in reduced dynamics, but this is turbulence/diagnostic evidence rather than a proof inequality
  + [source_005] is Carbone and Bragg, Generation of intense dissipation in high Reynolds number turbulence
    = url: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9289790/
    = relevance: describes strain self-amplification, depletion by vortex stretching, and redistribution by pressure Hessian in turbulent dynamics

& [ResearchResolution] is the pressure-coupling result
  + [confirmed_001_full_terms_matter] is pressure Hessian, viscosity, advection, and strain-vorticity interaction cannot be ignored when judging strain self-amplification
  + [confirmed_002_model_blowup_is_warning] is reduced strain self-amplification blowup shows that exact shared identities are insufficient without the full coupling structure
  + [confirmed_003_pressure_hessian_is_not_yet_sign_control] is pressure Hessian appears as redistribution or perturbative/full-equation structure, not as a known global coercive sign mechanism closing continuation
  + [confirmed_004_vorticity_interaction_is_promising] is strain-vorticity interaction gives a sharper way to inspect depletion of nonlinearity and advection effects
  + [confirmed_005_no_solution_claim] is no checked source supplies an autonomous one-sided inequality closing global smoothness for arbitrary smooth data

